rComments: Dr Brannen was genuinely a wonderful professor. Assignments were super clear cut, and although there was group work, in my experience it was alright, and she tried to make it easy on us. Lectures were entertaining, and she did her best to get everyone involved. Definitely take this prof if you have the chance!
She is the cutest prof I've met so far, super nice lady who sent me an email to apologize for calling my name wrong in class. Lots of breakout discussions though.

Kathleen is super nice! She can go through stuff quickly and has high-ish expectations but she's awesome at answering questions so just ask if you don't get something. I didn't do the textbook reading but I did check it out for the assignments and since its free on the library its worth checking out.

Absolutely lovely professor! Kathleen was so understanding and reasonable of online learning, very manageable workload. She extended out final project due date and gave us a week off just to rest when things were getting super stressful. Sweetest prof you could have, always willing to discuss content/assignments outside of class :)
She is so caring for her students. She is available to have a zoom to help you and really cares about your success. Amazing prof.
Loved having her! She is so caring for her students.
Sweet prof, passionate.

She is a sweet prof, Course had 8 homeworks (about 1 every week), 2 midterms and a final. No pop quizzes. I found that the lectures did not have all the content needed to do the homework (kinda hard), but the exams were mainly from her slides. She can be a bit vague at times. Requires work, but your mark will mainly reflect the work you put in.

You'll never meet a prof who cares more about her students than her. She tries to remember everyones names, she makes lectures interesting by having you watch videos or work with others. She's always accessible out of class for any question you might have, even stupid ones so don't be scared to ask her because she genuinely seems happy to help

Mrs Brannen is an excellent teacher. She genuinely cares about her students and is consistently ready to answer all of the questions. However, Pronunciation III itself isn't a fun course. The content reviewed in class can sometimes be difficult. It's not the teacher's fault. Overall, Mrs Brannen is an amazing teacher that wants you to succeed.

Madame Brannen est très gentille, mais sa charge de travail n'a absolument aucun sens. Au cours de la session, nous avons fait 5 courtes rédactions, 2 résumés critiques, 1 présentation orale, 2 examens et avons tout de même une proposition de recherche valant 30% en tant que travail final. Le cours manque de structure et est beaucoup trop chargé!

Lectures were fairly boring however she posts them all online. If you know the slides attendance and textbook are completely unnecessary. However, beware of the weekly pop quizzes which are very specific and ambiguously-worded. Easy course and grader, however, the class was not very engaging.

Prof. Brannen is a lovely person. She obviously cares about her students and is very understanding. Unfortunately, Speech Production is a very dry course and demands an extreme amount of memorization but she does her best to make sense of it. If there was a part of the test that most people didn't do well on she'd take it out. I would recommend her

Brannen is a very nice person, as others have mentioned. She is also very clear about what will be on quizzes and exams. However, for an introductory course in LIN1300, I found her teaching style to be slightly unclear. It's a complex subject with a lot of terminology that she doesn't always explicitly explain. She is available in office though.

Nice lady, decent professor! You can tell she cares about her students but unfortunately, her teaching isn't the best. Dry lectures with a lot of information and then gives a pop quiz that asks for the littlest things. Overall, meh!

Kathleen is probably the nicest prof I have ever had! She is so helpful after class and wants all her students to do well - go to her office hours she gives good hints for midterms ;). Midterms were very fair, however I hated her pop quizzes, not super difficult but you just always had to be at class (can be hard when you have it on Monday at 8:30)

Extremely nice lady, very caring, and easy to approach. Mini tests every week worth 2%, a midterm and a final. The content is a bit difficult if you are not very analytical, but with some effort it is possible to succeed well in this course. She was sometimes not very clear, and her marking scheme seemed arbitrary, but I would take again.
Very nice lady. The lectures are very interesting.

She is a very nice lady and she'll be happy to discuss any topic related to Linguistics, especially Phonology. However, her exams are very specific and the questions are not always evaluating important aspects of the content. You have to study every single detail. Also, some of her questions are unclear or ambiguous. Do not expect an A+.

Kathleen is obviously passionnate about her field of study. She's nice and fun to have as a teacher. However, I find that she tends to teach concepts a little fast, and it's hard to keep up with her sometimes because the concepts are not understood by everyone.

Kathleen obviously knows her stuff, and could answer almost any question the students had (even random ones). I had difficulty and she spend a full half hour helping me during office hours. I appreciated that greatly. However, I  found her class to be a bit too fast-paced and some important topics were glossed over quickly.

this was a great class. she tried to explain things but sometimes seemed a little unsure of herself. assignments and test questions ere quite ambiguous, however she made up for her ambiguity in her generous grading. would definitely recommend as a prof!
She is not clear and not sure of herself. She goes through the material fast and even if its new information, she won't spend to much time on it. She wants to help, but can't do it in a class.

Prof clearly wants to help her students; always available to meet students outside of class for extra help on assignments. Assignments and midterm are difficult; final project was fun and interesting (lots of freedom). She seems to know her material well enough, but is out of place in front of the class. Overall nice prof, alright course.

She is not very sure of herself and sometimes gives false information. Contradicts herself from one slide to the next of her powerpoint. She is very boring but at least she has a powerpoint with all her notes. A project worth 70% and three assignments worth 10% each -- fairly well separated. She is an easy grader for the most part.
